<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 04 at 10:15AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow and poor visibility over Marias Pass this morning...
Periods of light snow and poor visibility will continue to affect
portions of Highway 2 from west of Browning to Marias Pass this
morning. Visibility will be reduced to less than one mile at
times, with new snow accumulations up to an inch.
Those traveling in this region this morning should be prepared
for snow covered and slippery roadways, along with poor
visibility.</description>
